• Boston in state of virtual lockdown
• Police officer shot dead on MIT campus
• Detectives link shootout and marathon blasts</p><div class=\"author\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/profile/warrenmurray\">Warren Murray</a></div><div class=\"author\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/profile/matthewweaver\">Matthew Weaver</a></div><div class=\"author\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/profile/paulowen\">Paul Owen</a></div><br/><p style=\"clear:both\" />" "http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/2013/apr/19/boston-mit-police-dead-watertown" (20849 9266) old 5 nil nil ((title nil "Boston bombings: one suspect killed, one on the loose – live updates") (link nil "http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/2013/apr/19/boston-mit-police-dead-watertown") (description nil "<p>• Manhunt for second suspect in Watertown
