shot wounds, according to a statement from law enforcement officials in Cambridge. The men they hijacked a black Mercedes SUV, holding the driver at gunpoint for about 30 minutes before releasing him uninjured. Police pursued the vehicle into Watertown, with the men reportedly throwing explosives from the car and exchanging fire with officers.</p><p>On  Friday, the dead officer was named by the Middlesex County district attorney as Sean Collier, 26, of Somerville.</p><p>On Friday, Boston's CBS affiliate WBZ broadcast an interview procured by a local station in Maryland with a man, Alvi Tsarni, who said he was an uncle of the suspects.</p><p>Tsarni told the reporter that he had heard about his nephews' involvement this morning from a sister-in-law. \"She was crying and she said that Tamerlan was killed.\"</p><p>\"I can't believe this, it's not possible. My nephews can't do this,\" Tsarni said. \"I don't believe any of my nephews [are] involved in this horrible incident.\"</p><p>Tsarni said the brothers, Dzhokhar and Tamerlan, \"grew up in Kyrgyzstan\" and came to the United States \"seven or eight years ago.\"</p><p>In imperfect English, Tsarni, who said he had lived in the United States for 10 years, said he had not spoken with the brothers for a long time because of \"problems family.\" Then \"yesterday he called me,\" Tsarni said – he appeared to be referring to Tamerlan – \"and said 'Forgive me, and we will talk to this now. From now we will be together ever.\"</p><p>The reporter told Tsarni she was sorry for his loss.</p><p>\"I'm sorry too, if he did this one I'm sorry too. It's crazy. It's not possible. I can't believe it … It's crazy. It's unbelievable.</p><p>According to eyewitness reports, the men got out of the car and threw an explosive device at police. Tamerlan Tsarnaev then ran towards police where he was either tackled or shot. His brother got back in the car, and drove it straight through the police line, heading west.</p><p>In the shootout, another officer, from the Massachusetts Bay Transportation Authority, was seriously wounded and is in hospital, it was revealed at the briefing on Friday morning.</p><p>In the photographs released by the FBI on Thursday, Dzhokhar Tsarnaev is seen wearing a grey hoodie and a white cap turned backwards. He has long, curly dark hair, and walked through the marathon crowd about five paces behind his brother.</p><p>Police have said Tamerlan Tsarnaev was spotted placing a black bag outside the Forum restaurant, close to one of the bomb epicentres shortly before it detonated. That video has not been made public.</p><div class=\"related\" style=\"float: left; margin-right: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;\"><ul><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/boston-marathon-explosions\">Boston Marathon explosions</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/boston\">Boston</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/massachusetts\">Massachusetts</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/usa\">United States</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/us-crime\">US crime</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/russia\">Russia</a></li></ul></div><div class=\"author\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/profile/adam-gabbatt\">Adam Gabbatt</a></div><div class=\"author\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/profile/miriam-elder\">Miriam Elder</a></div><div class=\"author\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/profile/edpilkington\">Ed Pilkington</a></div><br/><div class=\"terms\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk\">guardian.co.uk</a> &copy; 2013 Guardian News and Media Limited or its affiliated companies. All rights reserved. | Use of this content is subject to our <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/help/terms-of-service\">Terms & Conditions</a> | <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/help/feeds\">More Feeds</a></div><p style=\"clear:both\" />") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/world")) "Boston Marathon explosions") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/world")) "Boston") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/world")) "Massachusetts") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/world")) "United States") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/world")) "US crime") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/world")) "Russia") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/world")) "World news") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/publication")) "guardian.co.uk") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/tone")) "News") (pubDate nil "Fri, 19 Apr 2013 14:01:02 GMT") (guid nil "http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/2013/apr/19/boston-lockdown-bombings-suspect") (dc:creator nil "Adam Gabbatt, Miriam Elder, Ed Pilkington") (dc:subject nil "World news") (dc:date nil "2013-04-19T14:02:08Z") (dc:type nil "Article") (dc:identifier nil "407518333") (media:keywords nil "Boston Marathon explosions, Boston, Massachusetts, United States, US crime, Russia, World news") (media:content ((height . "84") (type . "image/jpeg") (width . "140") (url . "http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/audio/video/2013/4/19/1366378703866/Swat-teams-in-the-neighbo-005.jpg")) (media:credit ((scheme . "urn:ebu")) "Jessica Rinaldi/Reuters") (media:description nil "Swat teams in the neighbourhood in Watertown. Photograph: Jessica Rinaldi/Reuters")) (media:content ((height . "276") (type . "image/jpeg") (width . "460") (url . "http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/audio/video/2013/4/19/1366378713272/Swat-teams-in-the-neighbo-010.jpg")) (media:credit ((scheme . "urn:ebu")) "Jessica Rinaldi/Reuters") (media:description nil "Swat teams were sent to the Massachusetts town of Watertown. Governor Deval Patrick said: 'This is a serious situation.' Photograph: Jessica Rinaldi/Reuters")) (media:content ((height . "220") (type . "image/jpeg") (width . "220") (url . "http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2013/4/19/1366378801987/suspect-2-latest-001.jpg")) (media:credit ((scheme . "urn:ebu")) "fbi.gov")))) ("Boston suspect Dzhokhar Tsarnaev was pupil at Cambridge high school" "<div class=\"track\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://hits.guardian.co.uk/b/ss/guardiangu-feeds/1/H.25.4/64813?ns=guardian&pageName=Article%3Aboston-suspect-dzhokhar-tsarnaev-school%3A1896450&ch=World+news&c3=GU.co.uk&c4=Boston+Marathon+explosions+%28News%29%2CBoston+%28US+news%29%2CChechnya%2CMassachusetts+%28News%29%2CCrime+%28US%29%2CUS+news%2CRussia+%28News%29%2CWorld+news%2CEurope+%28News%29&c5=Unclassified%2CNot+commercially+useful&c6=Miriam+Elder&c7=2013%2F04%2F19+02%3A07&c8=1896450&c9=Article&c10=News&c13=&c19=GUK&c47=UK&c64=UK&c65=Boston+suspect+Dzhokhar+Tsarnaev+was+pupil+at+Cambridge+high+school&c66=News&c72=&c73=&c74=&c75=&h2=GU%2FNews%2FWorld+news%2FBoston+Marathon+explosions\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" /></div><p class=\"standfirst\">19-year-old previously attended school in Dagestan, near Chechnya, and gives world view as 'Islam' on Russian social network site</p><p>Dzhokhar Tsarnaev, 19, has been identified as the surviving suspect in the Boston Marathon blast. Photographs of Tsarnaev, currently the subject of a massive manhunt, appear to match the man who became known as \"suspect number two\" or \"the suspect in the white hat\".</p><p>Tsarnaev's father, Anzor, told the Associated Press his son was a smart and accomplished young man. Speaking from Makhachkala, the capital of Dagestan, he said: \"My son is a true angel. Dzhokhar is a second-year medical student in the US. He is such an intelligent boy. We expected him to come on holidays here.\"</p><p>According to <a href=\"http://vk.com/id160300242\" title=\"\">Tsarnaev's account on the Russian social networking site VKontakte</a>, he graduated from Boston's <a href=\"http://crls.cpsd.us/\" title=\"\">Cambridge Rindge & Latin School</a> in 2011, having attended School No 1 in Makhachkala from 1999 to 2001.</p><p>He appears to have been a good student, apparently receiving a <a href=\"http://www.boston.com/yourtown/news/cambridge/2011/05/cambridge_announces_2011_city.html\" title=\"\">$2,500 scholarship from the city of Cambridge</a> in 2011 to pursue college. He was named a wrestling all-star at his high school in the same year.</p><p>On his VKontakte page, Tsarnaev says he considers \"career and money\" most important in life. As his world view, he wrote: \"Islam.\"</p><p>The page says Tsarnaev speaks English, Russian and Chechen, and belongs to a number of groups devoted to <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/chechnya\" title=\"\">Chechnya</a>. Dagestan, a republic neighbouring Chechnya, maintains a small Chechen minority.</p><p>Tsarnaev was born on 22 July 1993, just before a fierce battle for independence broke out in the republic of Chechnya, which attempted to secede from Russia in the wake of the Soviet Union's collapse. Over time, the independence movement grew increasingly Islamist in character. Largely quashed by Moscow, a low-level insurgency persists in Chechnya and has leaked into neighbouring Dagestan.</p><p>On VKontakte, Tsarnaev follows several pages devoted to Islam. He also lists one of his favourite songs as \"Hey Sexy Lady\" by Shaggy.</p><p>An acquaintance from high school told the Guardian that Tsarnaev appeared to be a \"very relaxed\" person, in contrast to his brother.</p><div class=\"related\" style=\"float: left; margin-right: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;\"><ul><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/boston-marathon-explosions\">Boston Marathon explosions</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/boston\">Boston</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/chechnya\">Chechnya</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/massachusetts\">Massachusetts</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/us-crime\">US crime</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/usa\">United States</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/russia\">Russia</a></li><li><